<!-- FAQ LANDING  -->

<div class="jumbotron mb-0 text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">What makes Photo Walks different?</h1>
    <hr class="my-4">
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
        <p class="col-lg-8">A photo walk is an activity in which photography enthusiasts gather in a group to walk around a certain area with the goal of taking pictures of people, places and things that seem interesting to them. Our photo walks begin with a short introductory coffee and end with a critique session so you can share your work and interact with other creative minds, and during the photo walk, our tour guides are open to providing cultural insights and travel tips. All you need for one of our photo walks is any form of camera and we will take care of the rest so you can focus on learning about Colombian culture, having fun and, of course, take great pictures of your trip! </p>
    </div>
    <p>
        If you have more questions about anything related to photo walks visit our FAQ!
    </p>
    <a class="btn btn-success btn-lg" href="/faq" role="button">Photo Walks Colombia FAQ</a>
</div>

